list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a person or animal) use the teeth to cut into or through something.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: he bit off a piece of cheese
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Anh ta cắn một miếng phô mai

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a fish) take the bait or lure on the end of a fishing line into the mouth.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: I marvel at how easily and eagerly a chub will bite
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Tôi ngạc nhiên về cách dễ dàng và háo hức một chub sẽ cắn

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: make firm contact with a surface.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the brake pads don't bite until they're warmed up
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Các má phanh không cắn cho đến khi chúng ấm lên

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a policy or situation) take effect, with unpleasant consequences.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the cuts in art education were starting to bite
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: những vết cắt trong giáo dục nghệ thuật đã bắt đầu cắn

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: an act of biting something in order to eat it.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: Stephen ate a hot dog in three big bites
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Stephen ăn một con chó nóng trong ba vết cắn lớn

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: a piece cut off by biting.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: Robyn took a large bite out of her sandwich
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Robyn cắn một miếng lớn ra khỏi bánh sandwich của mình
